<Layout title="Wound & Skin Assessment Tools" description="Wound and skin assessment tools used in nursing">
  <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`} class="back-link">← Back to all categories</a>
  <div class="badge">Wound &amp; Skin Assessment</div>
  <h1>Wound &amp; Skin Assessment Tools</h1>
  <p>Standardized tools for classifying, measuring, and monitoring wound healing, burn injuries, and skin conditions.</p>

  <div class="tool-list">
    <h2>Assessment Tools</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>NPUAP/NPIAP Pressure Injury Staging</strong> — Stages I–IV plus Unstageable and Deep Tissue Injury: Stage I (non-blanchable erythema), Stage II (partial thickness), Stage III (full thickness), Stage IV (tissue exposure). Updated 2016 guidelines use term "pressure injury."</li>
      <li><strong>BWAT (Bates-Jensen Wound Assessment Tool)</strong> — 15-item wound assessment tool measuring size, depth, edges, undermining, necrotic tissue type/amount, exudate type/amount, skin color, edema, and more. Scores 13–65.</li>
      <li><strong>Wagner Grading System</strong> — Diabetic foot ulcer classification Grades 0–5: 0 (intact skin/at risk) to 5 (whole foot gangrene). Guides intervention and amputation risk.</li>
      <li><strong>MEASURE Tool</strong> — Wound assessment acronym: Measure, Exudate, Appearance, Suffering, Undermining/tunneling, Re-evaluate, Edge. Provides structured wound documentation framework.</li>
      <li><strong>ABCDE Rule</strong> — Melanoma screening: Asymmetry, Border irregularity, Color variation, Diameter &gt;6 mm, Evolution (change over time). Used in skin cancer surveillance.</li>
      <li><strong>TBSA (Total Body Surface Area)</strong> — Burn estimation expressed as percentage of body surface area affected; critical for burn fluid resuscitation calculations (Parkland formula).</li>
      <li><strong>Lund and Browder Chart</strong> — Age-specific burn surface area estimation; more accurate than Rule of Nines for children as it adjusts for head-to-leg proportions by age.</li>
      <li><strong>Rule of Nines</strong> — Adult burn surface area estimation: head 9%, each arm 9%, chest/abdomen 18% front, back 18%, each leg 18%, genitalia 1%.</li>
      <li><strong>PASI (Psoriasis Area Severity Index)</strong> — Psoriasis severity index combining area affected and intensity of erythema, induration, and scaling; range 0–72. Used in treatment trials.</li>
      <li><strong>SCORAD (SCORing Atopic Dermatitis)</strong> — Combines atopic dermatitis extent (0–100%), intensity (0–18), and subjective symptoms (0–20). Total 0–103.</li>
      <li><strong>MASD Classification (Moisture-Associated Skin Damage)</strong> — Categorizes skin damage from incontinence (IAD), wound exudate (periwound MASD), perspiration (intertriginous dermatitis), or stoma/fistula output.</li>
      <li><strong>STAR Skin Tear Classification</strong> — Three-category system for skin tear severity: Category 1 (skin flap can be repositioned), Category 2 (partial flap loss), Category 3 (total flap loss).</li>
      <li><strong>IAD Staging (Incontinence-Associated Dermatitis)</strong> — Severity staging from normal skin (Stage 0) to persistent erythema, erosion, and infection (Stages 1–2) from moisture/irritant exposure.</li>
      <li><strong>REEDA Scale</strong> — Perineal wound healing assessment: Redness, Edema, Ecchymosis, Discharge, Approximation. Scores 0–3 for each domain; total 0–15.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
